---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const baseUrl = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
const basePath = baseUrl.endsWith('/') ? baseUrl : `${baseUrl}/`;
---

<BaseLayout title="About | Robert Otieno" description="About Robert Otieno, Enterprise Identity, Security & IT Operations Architect.">
	<section class="profile-section">
		<div class="profile-container">
			<div class="profile-header">
				<h1>Robert Otieno</h1>
				<p class="profile-title">Enterprise Identity, Security & IT Operations Architect</p>
				<div class="profile-meta">
					<span class="meta-item">📍 Copenhagen, Denmark</span>
					<span class="meta-item">🇰🇪 Kenyan</span>
					<span class="meta-item">⚡ Age 32</span>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="profile-grid">
				<div class="profile-bio">
					<h2>About Me</h2>
					<p>
						My roots trace back to Nyakach in Kisumu County, Kenya — a place that shaped my identity long before I began designing digital ones. Football was my first serious ambition. I trained and competed with the dream of going professional. The pitch taught me structure, spatial awareness, discipline, and resilience under pressure. Even today, I still play — not for trophies, but for the pure joy of the game. Football keeps me grounded. It reminds me that progress is built on repetition, teamwork, and belief.
					</p>
					<p>
						My journey into technology began in Kenya. That's where curiosity met opportunity — where I first started exploring systems, infrastructure, and the mechanics behind digital environments. But the trajectory shifted significantly when I moved to Denmark as a research assistant. That environment accelerated my thinking. It exposed me to deeper architectural problems — identity, trust boundaries, governance models, and privacy-engineered systems. That's where I found my field.
					</p>
					<p>
						Today, instead of reading defensive lines, I model trust relationships. Instead of anticipating strikers, I anticipate threat vectors. Instead of building match stamina, I design systems built for long-term resilience. I now operate at the intersection of enterprise governance, operational security, and emerging identity standards. My work spans IAM, IGA, PAM, and decentralized identity architectures — always with a focus on aligning technical controls with business strategy. To me, identity is not just access management; it is organizational trust infrastructure.
					</p>
					<p>
						I remain a dedicated Manchester United supporter. I still play football for fun. Because joy matters. Balance matters. And high performance requires both intensity and recovery. From aspiring professional footballer to security architect — the ambition never disappeared. It simply evolved. The field changed. The competition changed. The level stayed high.
					</p>
				</div>

				<div class="profile-education">
					<h2>Education & Background</h2>
					<div class="education-item">
						<h3>Research Assistant</h3>
						<p class="education-meta">Denmark · Early Career</p>
						<p>Initial transition into technology, exploring research in [field of focus], establishing foundation in [key research area].</p>
					</div>
					<div class="education-item">
						<h3>University/Degree</h3>
						<p class="education-meta">[Institution] · [Year]</p>
						<p>Major: [Your degree field]. Key focus areas: [relevant coursework or specializations].</p>
					</div>
					<div class="education-item">
						<h3>Professional Certifications</h3>
						<ul>
							<li>CISSP (Certified Information Systems Security Professional) - [Year]</li>
							<li>Additional certifications and credentials - [Add your certs here]</li>
						</ul>
					</div>
					<h3 style="margin-top: 1.5rem; color: #1e3a8a;">Interests & Passions</h3>
					<ul style="list-style: none; padding: 0; margin-top: 0.8rem;">
						<li>⚽ Football enthusiast & Manchester United supporter</li>
						<li>🔐 Enterprise security and identity architecture</li>
						<li>🚀 Technology innovation and emerging standards</li>
						<li>🌍 Building resilient systems for global enterprises</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section>
		<h2>Principles</h2>
		<div class="grid">
			<article class="card">
				<h3>Identity as Control Plane</h3>
				<p>Security posture starts with reliable identity context and consistent access decisions.</p>
			</article>
			<article class="card">
				<h3>Operational Integration</h3>
				<p>Policy value is realized only when IAM controls are embedded in incident and change workflows.</p>
			</article>
			<article class="card">
				<h3>Privacy by Architecture</h3>
				<p>Privacy is treated as a design constraint, not an afterthought, with explicit minimization choices.</p>
			</article>
			<article class="card">
				<h3>Automation for Scale</h3>
				<p>Governance must be repeatable, auditable, and operationally sustainable across enterprise growth.</p>
			</article>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section>
		<h2>Current Direction</h2>
		<p>
			I am focused on enterprise IAM modernization, access governance transformation, and practical pathways for decentralized identity in
			real-world organizations.
		</p>
	</section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
	.profile-section {
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #f8faff 0%, #ffffff 100%);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: clamp(1.5rem, 5vw, 2.5rem);
		margin-bottom: 2rem;
		border: 1px solid #e0e7ff;
	}

	.profile-container {
		max-width: 1200px;
		margin: 0 auto;
	}

	.profile-header {
		text-align: center;
		margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
		padding-bottom: 2rem;
		border-bottom: 2px solid #1e3a8a;
	}

	.profile-header h1 {
		font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
		color: #0f172a;
		margin: 0 0 0.5rem 0;
		font-weight: 800;
		letter-spacing: -0.02em;
	}

	.profile-title {
		font-size: 1.1rem;
		color: #1e3a8a;
		font-weight: 600;
		margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
	}

	.profile-meta {
		display: flex;
		justify-content: center;
		gap: 1.5rem;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
	}

	.meta-item {
		font-size: 0.95rem;
		color: #475569;
		font-weight: 500;
	}

	.profile-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 1.2fr 1fr;
		gap: 2.5rem;
	}

	.profile-bio h2,
	.profile-education h2 {
		font-size: 1.5rem;
		color: #0f172a;
		margin: 0 0 1.2rem 0;
		font-weight: 700;
		border-bottom: 2px solid #1e3a8a;
		padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
	}

	.profile-bio p {
		font-size: 0.95rem;
		line-height: 1.7;
		color: #334155;
		margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
	}

	.profile-bio p:last-of-type {
		margin-bottom: 0;
	}

	.education-item {
		margin-bottom: 1.8rem;
	}

	.education-item h3 {
		font-size: 1rem;
		color: #0f172a;
		margin: 0 0 0.4rem 0;
		font-weight: 700;
	}

	.education-meta {
		font-size: 0.85rem;
		color: #1e3a8a;
		font-weight: 600;
		margin: 0 0 0.6rem 0;
	}

	.education-item p {
		font-size: 0.9rem;
		color: #475569;
		line-height: 1.6;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.education-item ul {
		list-style: none;
		padding: 0;
		margin: 0.6rem 0 0 0;
	}

	.education-item ul li {
		font-size: 0.9rem;
		color: #334155;
		padding-left: 1.5rem;
		margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
		position: relative;
	}

	.education-item ul li::before {
		content: "✓";
		position: absolute;
		left: 0;
		color: #1e3a8a;
		font-weight: bold;
	}

	.profile-education h3 {
		font-size: 1rem;
		color: #1e3a8a;
		margin: 1.5rem 0 0.8rem 0;
		font-weight: 700;
	}

	.profile-education ul {
		list-style: none;
		padding: 0;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.profile-education ul li {
		font-size: 0.9rem;
		color: #334155;
		padding-left: 1.8rem;
		margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
		position: relative;
		line-height: 1.5;
	}

	.profile-education ul li::before {
		content: "→";
		position: absolute;
		left: 0;
		color: #1e3a8a;
		font-weight: bold;
	}

	@media (max-width: 900px) {
		.profile-grid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
			gap: 2rem;
		}

		.profile-meta {
			flex-direction: column;
			gap: 0.8rem;
		}

		.profile-header h1 {
			font-size: 1.8rem;
		}
	}

	@media (max-width: 600px) {
		.profile-section {
			padding: 1rem;
			margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
		}

		.profile-header {
			margin-bottom: 1.8rem;
			padding-bottom: 1.5rem;
		}

		.profile-header h1 {
			font-size: 1.5rem;
		}

		.profile-title {
			font-size: 0.95rem;
		}

		.profile-meta {
			gap: 0.8rem;
		}

		.meta-item {
			font-size: 0.85rem;
		}
	}
</style>